user.biography: Korean born, I love to cook & eat delicious food! I teach Korean cooking on YouTube & my website & I wrote 2 bestselling books. Let’s cook together! 🔨

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maangchi in Manhattan, New York. May be an image of dessert and indoor.

node.text: My new video is online! It’s a traditional Korean pressed cookie called dasik, made with all-natural ingredients. Check out my 4 different colors of dasik!

node.text: I felt like bulgogi that tastes like it’s cooked on charcoal. So I made my easy bulgogi last night! It tastes amazing! 😋

node.text: What did I buy at the Union Square greenmarket?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maangchi in Hell's Kitchen. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: My new video is online! Making hwajeon, disc shaped pan-cooked rice cake with flowers on top!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maangchi on August 05, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Spicy cold noodles(bibIm-naengmyeon). It’s my favorite these days!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maangchi on July 28, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: My new video is online!  Korean rolled omelette called gyeran-Mari! Enjoy it!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maangchi on July 22, 2021. May be an image of food and drink.

node.text: This dongchimi in my refrigerator makes me so happy!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maangchi in Hell's Kitchen. May be an image of food.

node.text: I made bo-ssam (pork wraps) for today’s lunch. The pork turned out very tender and juicy, served with lettuce, ssamjang, and home-grown perilla leaves. It was perfect!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maangchi on July 14, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: My new recipe is online! Steamed shishito peppers called kkwari-gochujjim!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maangchi in Hell's Kitchen. May be an image of food.

node.text: It summertime so I made cold noodle soup with yeolmu kimchi (young radish kimchi)!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maangchi in Hell's Kitchen. May be an image of food.

node.text: My new recipe is online! Green onion kimchi (pa-kimchi)!
